Ten people were injured Thursday morning on Umgeni Road after a taxi collided with a car near North Coast Road in Durban, ER24 paramedics said in a statement. ER24 spokesperson Werner Vermaak said: At approximately 6.30am paramedics from ER24 and other services arrived on the scene where they found the taxi off the road into nearby trees. Vermaak said 10 taxi passengers were found with minor to moderate injuries. Paramedics treated the injured for scrapes and bruises before they were transported to Addington Hospital. None of the occupants in the light motor vehicle sustained any injuries. The exact circumstances surrounding the collision is not yet known. Authorities are investigating.